This paper discusses the topic of clickbait in the field of education, which involves analyzing the content of educational videos. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are covered in cs.CL and cs.IR respectively. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to detect clickbait, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the metrics used to gauge the likeness factor for educational videos, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
